<h2 local-id=3D"5142e45e408a" id=3D"bitloopsinit-2.Overview">2. Overview</h=
2>
<p local-id=3D"a2ce0a659ad3"><code>bitloops init</code> initialises Bitloop=
s agent integrations for one or more supported AI coding agents by writing =
or merging hook configuration files.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"4b512b4a55dc" id=3D"bitloopsinit-Problemstatement">Problem =
statement</h3>
<p local-id=3D"a2be3def9c35">Bitloops session lifecycle and checkpoint work=
flows depend on agent hook events being wired correctly. Without a single i=
nitialisation command, users must configure each agent manually, which is e=
rror-prone, inconsistent across tools, and difficult to reproduce in team o=
r automation contexts.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"d08aa41490fc" id=3D"bitloopsinit-Goals">Goals</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"7c9fe9beb78f">
<li local-id=3D"3b4f8e87e91f">
<p local-id=3D"678566bef843">Provide one command to initialise supported ag=
ent integrations (<code>claude-code</code>, <code>codex</code>, <code>curso=
r</code>, <code>gemini-cli</code>, <code>opencode</code>).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4e6b6ba9095e">
<p local-id=3D"81cceec11e81">Support both explicit targeting (<code>--agent=
</code>) and guided multi-agent setup (<code>bitloops init</code> interacti=
ve flow).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"535cc84c5201">
<p local-id=3D"8187d55ee869">Keep initialisation idempotent and safe to re-=
run, while supporting reinstalls via <code>--force</code>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6c20eb88694a">
<p local-id=3D"187d34a45e69">Preserve non-Bitloops user configuration where=
 installers merge settings.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"258343dec4e5">
<p local-id=3D"23ebb5d833ad">Handle telemetry consent deterministically acr=
oss interactive and non-interactive environments.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"3fd697cfcd85" id=3D"bitloopsinit-Non-goals">Non-goals</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"efd1c1941822">
<li local-id=3D"5396ffd87dfb">
<p local-id=3D"fa73587e72cb">Enabling or disabling Bitloops project strateg=
y/settings (handled by <code>bitloops enable</code>/<code>disable</code>).<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0a43727240ac">
<p local-id=3D"8ce9f5d02775">Executing runtime hook event handling logic (h=
andled by <code>bitloops hooks ...</code> commands).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f7a8796807fe">
<p local-id=3D"cae26557f587">Managing unsupported agents outside the curren=
t built-in set.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"776e47ec9091">
<p local-id=3D"fde76bf07cc3">Designing a new UX beyond current command cont=
racts.</p></li>
</ul>
