<li local-id=3D"1edca46e2378">
<p local-id=3D"3851d526843f">Need to improve the git detection to allow for=
 monorepos and be able to use the cli from within any folder. When we run a=
ny command except init, we should search upwards for the closest git repo a=
nd .bitloops config and use that. For init, we should search upwards for th=
e closest .bitloops settings. If we reach the user home .bitloops or don=E2=
=80=99t find .bitloops at all then if we are within a .git level we are tal=
king about a regular repo whereas when we are at a lower level than the .gi=
t then we are looking at a monorepo setup. In the case of a monorepo where =
the .bitloops already exists at the .git level, then we are effectively cre=
ating override settings for the specific project and we should at least dis=
play a notice if not require confirmation. If we decide to go with confirma=
tion then in the --non-interactive mode, we would require an explicit flag =
in order to not return an error.</p></li>
</ul>
